dcterms:creator: L. Coelho
A. Shariff

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of 49 Hoechst-stained images with a size of 1344x1024 pixels, containing a total of 2212 cell nuclei. The dataset is challenging due to strong auto-fluorescence artifacts, visible debris, significant intensity inhomogeneities, and many closely clustered or partially overlapping cell nuclei.
dcterms:title: NIH3T3 dataset

dcterms:creator: L. Coelho
A. Shariff
R. Murphy
dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of 48 images of U2OS cells stained with Hoechst 33342, each with a size of 1349x1030 pixels, including 1836 cell nuclei. The dataset is challenging due to frequent occurrences of strongly non-elliptical and closely clustered cell nuclei.
dcterms:title: U2OS dataset

dcterms:description: Two datasets of GFP-transfected mouse embryonic stem cells from the IEEE ISBI Cell Tracking Challenge training data, consisting of temporal image sequences with sizes of 1024x1024 pixels. The datasets include 31 images with 150 cell nuclei and 20 images with 128 cell nuclei, challenging due to low signal-to-noise ratio and low image contrast.
dcterms:title: GOWT1 datasets

dcterms:description: A dataset containing 175 3-D stacks of 35–50 DAPI-stained images of human Fibroblast cells, with each image sized 1024x1024 pixels, including 985 cell nuclei. The dataset is challenging due to partially strong intensity inhomogeneities of the cell nuclei.
dcterms:title: Fibroblast dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of 25 DAPI-stained images of HeLa cells, containing a total of 282 cell nuclei, with each image sized 1200x1620 pixels. The dataset is used for evaluating segmentation methods.
dcterms:title: HeLa dataset
